{
  "texts": [
    "It has been extended to the twisted setting by Labourie [Lab08].",
    "For ρ-equivariant maps h: ( B, c) → (G/K, g sym), the tensor h * g sym on B is π 1 (B)-invariant, and hence defines a tensor on B 2.",
    "In particular, the energy density e ǧ (h) = tr ǧ h * g sym is a function on B 2.",
    "Since B 2 is compact, h: ( B, c) → (G/K, g sym) has a well-defined energy:E(h) = B e ǧ (h) dvol ǧ.The 2-form e ǧ (h) dvol ǧ is conformally invariant, so E depends only on the conformal class c and not on the choice of ǧ ∈ c. Thus, we can define a function E: Teich(B) → R ≥0 byE ρ (c) = inf{E(h): h ρ -equivariant},where Teich(B) is the Teichmüller space of B 2, the space of marked conformal structures on B 2.",
    "The infimum is attained [Lab08, Thm."
  ]
}